  Locus:
    Page: 10
    Verse: 1
Tags:
  - Adversity
---
The most generous vine, if not pruned, runs out into many superfluous stems
and grows at last weak and fruitless; so doth the best man if he be not cut
short in his desires, and pruned with afflictions.
